{[#]White has a rather simple plan at his disposal: Ne8 or Nh5 (threatening
Nf6), then after ...Bh8, return the knight to g7, and finally attack the
bishop with Kg8. In order to prevent this plan Black must play actively with
his king. ---} 1... Ke5 $1 {Preparing a king raid to f5.} ({Also possible is} 
1... Kd5 2. Ne8 Bh8 3. Ng7 Ke5 {in the same spirit - Lalic/Baburin, when} 4.
Kg8 {is met by} Kf6 {.}) ({Instead, the game went} 1... Kd7 $2 2. Ne8 Bh8 3.
Kg8 $2 ({we already know the correct move:} 3. Ng7 $1 {, preparing Kg8}) 3...
Bb2 {and a draw was agreed, although by} 4. Kf7 Bh8 5. Ng7 $1 {White could
still have won the game.}) 2. Ne8 Kf5 {. White can't make progress.} *

